# Key Business Insights

### Loan Analysis

- Private Banking customers contributed the highest loan portfolio.
- Medium-income customers accounted for the largest share of loans.
- Loan distribution varied significantly across occupations and customer segments.

### Deposit Analysis

- Private Banking customers maintained the highest deposits.
- Female customers showed strong contribution to deposit balances.
- Medium-income customers represented the largest deposit segment.

### Customer Analysis

- Banking relationship type strongly influenced financial activity.
- Income level played a major role in both lending and deposit behavior.
- Customer demographics revealed distinct banking preferences.

